trans-unit.source: Provides event data for ASP.NET mobile controls that support custom pagination.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.
The class <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.LoadItemsEventArgs> object provides event data with information about how many items to load into the control on demand.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.LoadItemsEventArgs"></xref> class.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.

Constructs a new <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.LoadItemsEventArgs> object, initializing the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.LoadItemsEventArgs.ItemIndex%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.LoadItemsEventArgs.ItemCount%2A> properties with the values of the `index`, and `count` parameters, respectively.
Initializes the <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.LoadItemsEventArgs.ItemIndex"></xref> property with this value.
Initializes the <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.LoadItemsEventArgs.ItemCount"></xref> property with this value.
Gets or sets the count of items in the control.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.
The count of items in the control.
Gets the index of the first item to be loaded by the invoked event.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.
The index of the first item to be loaded by the invoked event.
